  <description><![CDATA[<p>The new Hotel Panorama has an excellent location in <a data-udi="umb://document/5f7cf8fdbd684bd5bba7644eede878ac" href="/{localLink:umb://document/5f7cf8fdbd684bd5bba7644eede878ac}" title="Flaine">Flaine</a>, with its ski-in ski-out location it means you can easily explore the 145km of pistes that <a data-udi="umb://document/5f7cf8fdbd684bd5bba7644eede878ac" href="/{localLink:umb://document/5f7cf8fdbd684bd5bba7644eede878ac}" title="Flaine">Flaine</a> has to offer. </p>
<h2>Great value</h2>
<p><span>Enjoy an all-inclusive stay in this warm and welcoming hotel, where everything has been designed with families in mind. The benefit of being on an all inclusive basis means all your meals and drinks are included, you can fuel up for a day of exploring at the buffet breakfast and return for a bite to eat at lunch. Once the slopes have closed for the day you can sit back and relax with a drink and an après snack, often including sweet treats, and then get ready for the buffet dinner where there's a large choice of dishes for all tastes. The hotel also features a Savoyard themed restaurant which is by reservation only, so you can enjoy regional dishes.</span></p>
<h2>Family friendly</h2>
<p>Throughout the winter season there's also children's clubs hosted by the hotels own animation team, where the clubs are designed specifically for different age groups. The younger guests can enjoy arts and crafts, games, a range of activities and discos, whereas the older teens have their own areas throughout the hotel to chill out but can also take part in a range of activities hosted by the activity leaders.</p>
<h2>Fantastic location</h2>
<p>With a piste side location, it is incredibly easy to get onto the <span>Flaine Forêt slopes</span>, click on your skis or tighten your bindings and head down the green run next to the Grand Van chairlift where you have access to the 265km across the Le Grand Massif ski area. The ski school is just across the road, so it is really easy for those just starting out. </p>
<h2>Soothing spa and relaxation</h2>
<p>After a day on the slopes, enjoy relaxing in the hotels own wellness area featuring an indoor pool, sauna and hammam. If relaxing isn't for you, there's also a fully equipped fitness room with a range of equipment. Alternatively, make the most of the winter sun and sit back and relax on the sunny terrace with views of the surrounding slopes. </p>]]></description>
